Class Event

java.lang.Object
classes.Event
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Event>
public class Event extends Object implements Comparable<Event>
Class that declares the Event object. Events contain instances of other declared objects. Will be created and manipulated based on user input.
Author:
Abhishek Thakare, Adhit Thakur

    • testCompareToForEqualDates

      private static void testCompareToForEqualDates()
      Tests comparison between events with same Date using compareTo(). Compares timeslots to order them correctly. Prints "succeeded" if event 1 is before event 2 and output is -1, "failed" otherwise.

    • testTwoEventsEqual

      private static void testTwoEventsEqual()
      Tests if two created events are equal using equals(). Actual output should match the expected output of true. Prints "succeeded" if actual output is true, "failed" otherwise.

    • testTwoEventsNotEqual

      private static void testTwoEventsNotEqual()
